1
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:34,040
This dish is delicious.

2
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:36,800
Director Liao.

3
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:38,520
Here, Old Liao.

4
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:43,160
You all take your time eating.

5
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:43,920
I'm done.

6
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:49,320
Me being a culture and tourism ambassador,

7
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:50,920
here in Taohua Town,

8
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:52,640
it's really unprecedented.

9
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:55,760
I still don't know what I'm supposed to do.

10
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,240
Then you've got it all wrong.

11
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:59,480
Lots of places have tourism ambassadors.

12
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,560
Especially the ones with thriving tourism.

13
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:02,920
A tourism ambassador

14
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:03,960
is basically like a celebrity.

15
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,840
And your role as Taohua Town's ambassador

16
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:06,840
is no ordinary one.

17
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,400
The last one was Li Bai.

18
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,960
This one's you.

19
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:13,920
Then I'll be Wang Lun.

20
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:17,520
From now on, we'll team up to shoot short videos,

21
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,800
focused on culture and tourism content,

22
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:22,040
to drive traffic to our Xuan paper industry.

23
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:23,760
Forget it, forget it.

24
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,640
That's a young people's thing.

25
00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:26,400
I can't do it.

26
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,520
You definitely can.

27
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:30,160
I'll film, you talk.

28
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:32,360
With all the knowledge you've got,

29
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:33,520
if we do it right,

30
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:34,520
it could really go viral.

31
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:35,920
This is what's trending now.

32
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:37,840
Director Liao, this'll really work.

33
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,080
Let's start with our upcoming

34
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:40,720
Four Treasures of the Study Festival.

35
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:43,120
Really?

36
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:44,800
We'll get started this afternoon.

37
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,520
Once you're done eating, think about what to say.

38
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:48,520
Okay.

39
00:02:50,160 --> 00:02:52,520
I told everyone to meet here at one-thirty.

40
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,920
It's been over ten minutes already,

41
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:55,360
and not a single person's shown up.

42
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,080
Here they come.

43
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:09,520
Director Lin.

44
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:12,640
How are you late on the very first day?

45
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:13,280
We're not.

46
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:15,280
We left the town at one thirty.

47
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,440
We didn't waste a minute.

48
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:18,280
Yeah, one thirty is the start time.

49
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,560
That's the town's rule.

50
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:20,160
What I meant was...

51
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:21,000
Enough, Taozi.

52
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:22,760
Be clearer with the notice next time.

53
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:24,000
It's arrive by one thirty,

54
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,280
not leave at one thirty.

55
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:26,560
Got it.

56
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:28,080
Five people. Where are the other two?

57
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:29,760
You mean Wang Hao and the other one?

58
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:30,840
They've already gone in.

59
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,040
Okay, hurry up then.

60
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:35,960
What's wrong with me putting my stuff here?

61
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,160
I'm placing it right at my own doorstep.

62
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:38,000
How does that bother any of you?

63
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:38,680
Exactly!

64
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:40,080
How does it bother you?

65
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:42,080
Everyone, everyone, please.

66
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:42,960
Here's the thing.

67
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:44,600
The government has new regulations.

68
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:46,000
We're holding a new event.

69
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:48,080
This area is public land.

70
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:49,880
You've got to pack these up first.

71
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:51,080
For one, it's inconvenient.

72
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:51,600
And second,

73
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:53,320
it really looks bad, right?

74
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:54,760
I don't care how it looks.

75
00:03:54,760 --> 00:03:55,760
What's wrong with putting it here?

76
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:57,760
You're the one hurting our business.

77
00:03:57,760 --> 00:03:58,480
Am I right?

78
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:00,360
Yeah, you're cutting into our earnings!

79
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,080
We've always been set up here.

80
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:01,800
Everyone...

81
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,520
Fine, if you won't move it, I will.

82
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:05,080
You have to. Get out of the way!

83
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:05,840
What are you doing?

84
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:06,640
We're just not moving.

85
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:08,480
Come on, come on, haul me away then!

86
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:09,640
Come on, take me in, take me in!

87
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:10,400
Go on, take me away!

88
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,920
So you're gonna throw the first punch?

89
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:13,480
Did I hit anyone?

90
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,320
You're the one making a scene!

91
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:16,079
Boss Huo.

92
00:04:16,519 --> 00:04:18,399
Where would you like us to take you, Boss Huo?

93
00:04:18,399 --> 00:04:18,959
No, no.

94
00:04:18,959 --> 00:04:19,760
It's nothing, nothing.

95
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:20,880
Little Lin, here's the situation.

96
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:22,680
We've been set up here for ages.

97
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:24,840
Now suddenly we can't anymore?

98
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:26,160
Business is already lousy.

99
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:27,480
Isn't this taking food off our table?

100
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,000
Right?

101
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:28,920
Exactly.

102
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,520
Business is already tough.

103
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,560
That's why we're holding the Four Treasures Festival.

104
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,240
Right?

105
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:34,880
To help promote everyone, spread the word.

106
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:35,920
Isn't that a good thing?

107
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,360
See? Listen to what Little Lin said.

108
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,800
What was that attitude just now?

109
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:40,360
Why didn't you just say so from the start?

110
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,000
I...

111
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:43,480
I'll handle next year's tax rebate for your paper mill.

112
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:44,080
Hurry up.

113
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:45,320
I'll definitely pack up.

114
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:47,320
You've helped me out a lot before.

115
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,560
I haven't even had a chance to thank you.

116
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,800
Enough. If you really want to thank me,

117
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:51,360
get everyone to pack their stuff up, okay?

118
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:52,240
Everyone, folks.

119
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:53,440
Everyone, everyone, listen up.

120
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,240
Everyone, hear me out.

121
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:57,400
The government's holding an event

122
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,760
and we have to cooperate actively.

123
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:01,400
Forget just banning street stalls,

124
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,240
even if they shut our shops down

125
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,240
and starved us to death,

126
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,640
we'd still have to cooperate.

127
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:07,400
Hold on, what's that supposed to mean?

128
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:09,040
Boss Jiang.

129
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,520
Come on, Boss Jiang.

130
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:11,600
The association

131
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,040
already held a meeting for everyone.

132
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,120
We already explained

133
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:15,800
the purpose and meaning of this event.

134
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:18,680
No one's asking anyone to shut down, okay?

135
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:19,880
Look, sir,

136
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:21,520
the government holding an event

137
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:22,920
is meant for our own good.

138
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:24,840
But banning us from setting up stalls,

139
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:27,240
how's that any different from shutting down?

140
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:27,760
Exactly.

141
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:29,360
What's the point of this event then?

142
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:29,920
Right.

143
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:32,360
This expo will bring everyone

144
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:33,800
foot traffic you don't normally get.

145
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,400
It'll also boost everyone's sales.

146
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:36,520
Why aren't you mentioning that?

147
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:37,200
Xiao Lin,

148
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,400
you can't just say that.

149
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:40,520
Who can guarantee more foot traffic?

150
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:41,880
Who can guarantee more sales?

151
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:42,960
Banning us from setting up stalls now

152
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,400
is really affecting our livelihoods.

153
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:44,920
Am I right?

154
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:45,120
Yes.

155
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,440
That's the fundamental issue.

156
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,760
You need to listen to everyone's opinions.

157
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,560
You can't go against public will.

158
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,240
Business is tough these days,

159
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:55,760
we can't afford to gamble, right?

160
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:57,000
Right, right.

161
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:57,680
You people,

162
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,120
don't treat us like kids.

163
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,560
Making it all sound so nice,

164
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,840
isn't it just to score political points?

165
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:03,600
Exactly.

166
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:04,840
You wrote the script,

167
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:05,760
you play the leads,

168
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:06,880
and make us play extras.

169
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:08,120
You don't even feed us,

170
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,760
and then make us throw in our savings.

171
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,320
You're really working us over, huh?

172
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:12,880
Alright, alright, that's enough.

173
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:13,560
Okay.

174
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:15,440
Let me speak from the heart too.

175
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,560
Whether it's about political achievements

176
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:17,880
depends on what kind we're pursuing.

177
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,400
If holding this expo

178
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:21,440
can bring real, tangible benefits,

179
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:23,040
then I'll go after that achievement.

180
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:24,000
No one can stop me.

181
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:25,920
And for this expo,

182
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,560
the town is putting up money and effort,

183
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,560
providing materials to everyone for free.

184
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,200
If any of you can bring in

185
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:32,600
renowned calligraphers or painters,

186
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,040
we'll even waive your booth fees.

187
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,320
Are these just pretty words?

188
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,680
No, these are real actions.

189
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,880
If we all work together, we can make this

190
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:39,600
turn out even better.

191
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,640
Isn't that a good thing?

192
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:42,320
Of course, I know

193
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:44,120
everyone has lots of doubts.

194
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:45,040
That's alright.

195
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:47,200
Let's lay everything out clearly today,

196
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:47,880
alright?

197
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,080
Today, I, Lin Yiran, am going to...

198
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:49,800
Alright, alright, Lin Yiran.

199
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:50,560
That's enough.

200
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:52,840
All the bosses are right here.

201
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:53,560
Deputy Mayor Luo has arrived.

202
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:55,840
What's going on, Wang Hao?

203
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:57,800
I heard you got into an argument.

204
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:58,840
I didn't.

205
00:06:58,840 --> 00:06:59,560
Apologize.

206
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:01,240
Now.

207
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:04,360
I'm sorry.

208
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,120
It's fine.

209
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:06,640
My apologies.

210
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:07,360
It's alright, Mayor.

211
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,640
And you, Lin Yiran.

212
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,320
How many times have I told you?

213
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:12,880
Mind your attitude with the people.

214
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,040
Everyone, cool down.

215
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,320
There's no way around it.

216
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:16,520
There's just no other way.

217
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:18,440
Deputy Mayor Luo, we can count on you.

218
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:18,920
Brother Erhu.

219
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,200
We prefer dealing with

220
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,360
classy leaders like this.

221
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,120
No, no, no.

222
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,320
If we can't work it out,

223
00:07:23,320 --> 00:07:24,640
we'll go to the top brass.

224
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:25,400
No, no.

225
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:27,480
We can settle this without them.

226
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:28,840
Here's the thing.

227
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:31,040
On behalf of Taohua Town government,

228
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:33,080
I apologize to all of you bosses.

229
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,320
You all have complaints and thoughts,

230
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:38,080
which means we haven't done our job well.

231
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:40,200
Look at Deputy Mayor Luo's attitude.

232
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:41,760
Actually,

233
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:43,400
you all having opinions and thoughts,

234
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:46,240
fighting for your lawful rights,

235
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,840
I think that's a good thing.

236
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,600
As the government,

237
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:52,600
we exist to protect your rights.

238
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:54,760
Otherwise, how could we call it serving the people?

239
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:55,560
Am I right?

240
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:56,560
Right.

241
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,600
Look at Deputy Mayor Luo's awareness.

242
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,520
Yes, exactly.

243
00:07:58,520 --> 00:07:59,320
Thoughtful, very thoughtful.

244
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:00,120
Exactly, exactly.

245
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:01,760
Since we're all gathered here today,

246
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,240
let me say a few words.

247
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,440
Hosting this convention

248
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:07,000
has caused you all a lot of trouble.

249
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,240
It pains me too.

250
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,560
But there's no choice.

251
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:12,000
I hope you bosses will cooperate.

252
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,920
Here, I'll make you a promise.

253
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,760
Once the convention opens,

254
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:18,840
you bosses get first pick of the good booths,

255
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:20,560
to make up for your recent losses.

256
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:21,320
Alright?

257
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:22,440
Sure, no problem. Good, good.

258
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:24,440
Since you all trust me so much,

259
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:26,320
let's break it up now.

260
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:29,120
No sense hurting business, right?

261
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:31,880
Since Deputy Mayor Luo has promised,

262
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,559
let's cooperate actively.

263
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:33,880
Pack it up.

264
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:34,440
Pack up, pack up.

265
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:35,400
Alright, Brother Erhu.

266
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:35,760
Give me a hand.

267
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:36,559
Thank you, thank you.

268
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:40,760
I hadn't finished speaking.

269
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,800
Is this fair? Really?

270
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:48,560
This...

271
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,520
The booth layout doesn't even affect

272
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:51,680
their normal business.

273
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:53,680
The prime booths

274
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:56,040
are reserved for brush, ink, and inkstone vendors.

275
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:57,680
Just handing them over for free?

276
00:08:57,680 --> 00:08:59,120
What about the other exhibitors?

277
00:08:59,200 --> 00:08:59,880
Exactly.

278
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:01,040
Will they come again next time?

279
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:03,400
And booths are already tight.

280
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:04,600
If Deputy Mayor Luo handles it this way,

281
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:06,040
it means whoever makes a fuss wins,

282
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,240
whoever kicks up a fuss gets rewarded.

283
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,520
If we set this precedent,

284
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:10,880
the impact will be terrible.

285
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,440
If you have something to say, say it.

286
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,320
I disagree with Deputy Mayor Luo's approach.

287
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:21,080
Xiao Lin.

288
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:24,160
Deputy Mayor Luo nipped a potential

289
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:27,240
mass incident in the bud.

290
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,080
What's wrong with that?

291
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,160
Secretary Peng.

292
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:32,120
It's not that big a deal.

293
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,320
No need to be so serious.

294
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:34,880
Actually, this is between us two.

295
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:36,360
I'll just talk to her privately.

296
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,440
We won't bother you.

297
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:39,160
Xiao Lin, come on, back with me.

298
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,120
Let's go.

299
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:42,720
Deputy Mayor Luo.

300
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,200
How about this.

301
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:46,720
If you have things to do, go handle them.

302
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:48,040
Have a good talk.

303
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:49,920
I'll take my leave.

304
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,720
Do you know what you did wrong today?

305
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:06,840
Your attitude toward Deputy Mayor Luo.

306
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:11,640
The way Deputy Mayor Luo handles things

307
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:14,080
may not be perfect,

308
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:16,760
but at least he prevented something

309
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:18,480
from getting even worse.

310
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,120
You're in a leadership role now.

311
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:23,560
You have to see the bigger picture.

312
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:26,240
Use people's strengths, tolerate their flaws.

313
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:30,640
But his approach leaves problems behind.

314
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:32,600
It could cause even more trouble.

315
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:34,560
Then stay alert in everything,

316
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:36,720
and take everything seriously.

317
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,720
Don't give yourself a chance to slip up.

318
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,240
When we do our work,

319
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:42,760
it's not about how much power you hold,

320
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:45,560
it's about how heavy your responsibility is.

321
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,480
If you can't shoulder that responsibility,

322
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:49,120
no matter how much power you're given,

323
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:51,240
you won't make a good leader.

324
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:57,960
The current problem

325
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,760
isn't that our sales are bad,

326
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:02,240
it's that our production can't keep up.

327
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:04,360
So what do we do?

328
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,760
We can't just stop streaming, right?

329
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:07,840
You need to think this through carefully.

330
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,800
Our blind boxes from before

331
00:11:10,280 --> 00:11:12,720
were basically a form of scarcity marketing.

332
00:11:13,520 --> 00:11:15,760
Doing pre-sales works the same way.

333
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:17,640
As long as we build the right buzz

334
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:18,640
and promote it well,

335
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:20,920
then once our production ramps up,

336
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,520
our sales will explode.

337
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:24,640
Here's what we'll do.

338
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:26,400
You all, hold another meeting.

339
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:28,160
Work out a livestream plan and send it to me.

340
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:30,160
We'll meet again tomorrow morning, okay?

341
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:31,920
Good, get back to work then.

342
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:33,000
Okay, okay, okay.

343
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:38,640
You're just in time.

344
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:39,720
Help me grab my bag.

345
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:40,640
Go find Xuan Le.

346
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:41,320
Tell him about the next plan.

347
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:42,040
Sister Xin.

348
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:45,320
The cultural product copyright is registered.

349
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,520
Here's the photocopy they just sent.

350
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,720
Great, I'll take it to him.

351
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:48,400
Sister Xin.

352
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:51,400
You'd better take a look yourself.

353
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,960
The moment I noticed something off, I contacted

354
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,400
Director Xiang from the Shenzhen Copyright Department.

355
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:05,920
I explained to him

356
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:07,920
the copyright owner can't be Dayazhai.

357
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:09,640
It must be the designer himself.

358
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:11,000
How did he explain it?

359
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:14,560
He said it was ordered from above.

360
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:16,240
Above?

361
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:17,400
Above who exactly?

362
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:19,040
He didn't say outright.

363
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:21,560
I'm guessing it's the Chairman.

364
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:26,120
On what grounds?

365
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:28,120
When they thought he wasn't good enough, they pulled out.

366
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:30,320
Now that they see his value,

367
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:32,920
they've thrown away all shame and grab it by force.

368
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,160
So shameless.

369
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:35,840
Keep your voice down, Sister Xin.

370
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:37,560
I'm calling the Chairman right now.

371
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,160
Please calm down.

372
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:40,920
The bigger the issue, the more you need to stay calm.

373
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,720
With things at this point already,

374
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:44,640
how do they expect me to face Xuan Liang?

375
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,600
If this really is the Chairman's decision,

376
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,760
he must have prepared how to handle you.

377
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:50,200
What I mean is,

378
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:51,400
you need to think it through.

379
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:53,200
Find a solution that's best for Xuan Liang,

380
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:54,960
for Dayazhai, and for yourself too.

381
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,800
The best possible resolution.

382
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:59,520
We can't end up in a mutually destructive situation.

383
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:08,960
Hello?

384
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:10,880
Hello, Chairman.

385
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,560
Is now a good time?

386
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:13,640
Yes, go ahead.

387
00:13:13,920 --> 00:13:14,720
Director Xin,

388
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:17,480
your work lately at the Taohua Town branch

389
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:19,240
has been outstanding.

390
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:22,000
Truly remarkable achievements.

391
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:23,520
I need to throw you a celebration.

392
00:13:23,520 --> 00:13:24,320
You've worked hard.

393
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:26,120
Everyone's busy, I'm doing fine.

394
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,040
Chairman,

395
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,800
I just want to confirm something with you.

396
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:30,520
Do you know about Xuan Liang's cultural design

397
00:13:30,520 --> 00:13:32,000
copyright registration?

398
00:13:32,360 --> 00:13:33,240
Yes, I do.

399
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:34,480
Wasn't this matter

400
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:36,240
handed over to Director Xiang to handle?

401
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:36,840
What's wrong?

402
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:39,000
There's something you might not be aware of.

403
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,960
The copyright has now been registered,

404
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:44,240
and the holder is Dayazhai,

405
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:45,520
not Xuan Liang.

406
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:49,240
Are you wondering

407
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:51,120
why Xuan Liang's cultural design

408
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:53,840
got registered under Dayazhai's name?

409
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:56,840
Yes, I really want to know.

410
00:13:58,840 --> 00:13:59,720
Director Xin,

411
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:02,480
at the Taohua Town branch,

412
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:03,880
you mainly handle

413
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:08,120
thread-bound books and fine art business.

414
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:11,480
Working with a designer like Xuan Liang

415
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:12,760
is probably your first time.

416
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:15,840
But here at headquarters,

417
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:18,120
we've worked with all kinds of designers,

418
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:19,520
countless times.

419
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,120
Since we're on this topic today,

420
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:24,600
there are two things I must make clear to you.

421
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:25,280
First,

422
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:28,040
in every contract HQ signs with designers,

423
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:29,320
there's always this clause:

424
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:31,600
copyright belongs to Dayazhai.

425
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,640
Even for well-known designers,

426
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:37,160
the most they get is shared copyright.

427
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,720
I understand, Chairman.

428
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,880
But what if Xuan Liang later refuses

429
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:42,240
to keep working with us?

430
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,640
Then we simply won't work with him.

431
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:45,760
Director Xin,

432
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:48,880
I fully understand how you feel.

433
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:56,520
I had legal pull the contract you signed with Xuan Nan.

434
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:57,960
To be honest,

435
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,240
it was extremely unprofessional.

436
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:01,760
Once you've dealt with these designers long enough,

437
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:02,960
you'll understand.

438
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:06,240
We're the ones who gave them room to create,

439
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:08,240
even room to survive.

440
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:09,520
But what about them?

441
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:11,440
Without exception,

442
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:13,520
the moment their wings grow strong,

443
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:14,640
they all fly away.

444
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:17,320
See? That's human nature.

445
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:20,080
Da Ya Zhai isn't a charity.

446
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,280
It's not a training school.

447
00:15:21,280 --> 00:15:23,480
What we pursue is maximum profit.

448
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:24,240
Am I right?

449
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:25,520
Second,

450
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:28,120
copyright registration isn't Da Ya Zhai

451
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:29,520
deliberately targeting any one person.

452
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:31,400
Nor is it some scheme of ours.

453
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:34,480
Copyright registration is Da Ya Zhai's

454
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:36,160
standard procedure

455
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:38,640
with every single designer.

456
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,840
It's a necessary risk-avoidance measure,

457
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:44,040
also known as a self-protection mechanism.

458
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:46,120
From now on, and going forward,

459
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:49,240
all cultural products Xuan Nan creates with us,

460
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:50,680
their copyright registration

461
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:52,600
must be under Da Ya Zhai's name.

462
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:53,760
Have I made myself clear?

463
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:56,120
What angle you take when talking to him,

464
00:15:56,120 --> 00:15:58,880
and all the consequences that may follow,

465
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:01,520
you need to think through carefully yourself.

466
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:06,240
Stand here.

467
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:07,440
Let's set a spot, right here.

468
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:07,960
Okay.

469
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:10,680
Take a look.

470
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:13,880
Perfect, what a shot.

471
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:14,760
Let's start.

472
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:15,480
Three,

473
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:16,160
two,

474
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:16,840
one.

475
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,920
Hi everyone, I'm Old Liao.

476
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:22,520
Do you know just how much knowledge

477
00:16:22,520 --> 00:16:24,920
"learning that fills five carts" really contains?

478
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:27,520
Do you know the real story

479
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:30,240
behind "penetrating three-tenths into the wood"?

480
00:16:32,040 --> 00:16:32,880
Wait, hold on, wait.

481
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:34,240
Dir- Director Liao.

482
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:36,440
Aren't we supposed to be covering the Four Treasures of the Study?

483
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:37,240
Right, Director.

484
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:39,280
Did you not prepare your lesson properly?

485
00:16:40,360 --> 00:16:41,400
Posing questions,

486
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:43,840
sparking everyone's thirst for knowledge,

487
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:46,400
that's educational psychology.

488
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:49,040
Director Liao,

489
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:51,440
how long do you plan to talk?

490
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:52,880
This is a short video.

491
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,840
The point is short and sharp.

492
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,760
That's because they lack culture.

493
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:58,640
As long as it's told well,

494
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:00,880
no matter how long, it feels short.

495
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:04,119
Told poorly, even a short one drags on.

496
00:17:04,599 --> 00:17:06,400
It's the same principle

497
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,440
as Einstein's theory of relativity.

498
00:17:08,599 --> 00:17:09,160
Right.

499
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:10,000
Right.

500
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,599
Please, go on, go on.

501
00:17:56,120 --> 00:17:57,160
Xin Ran

502
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:58,120
You came just in time.

503
00:17:58,360 --> 00:17:59,080
Come over here.

504
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:03,800
Come, take a look at this.

505
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:08,120
This is...

506
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,360
This is Xuan Bao'er.

507
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:11,120
That's right.

508
00:18:11,360 --> 00:18:12,960
So? Isn't it fun?

509
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:14,520
Isn't it cool?

510
00:18:15,120 --> 00:18:15,880
Isn't it cute?

511
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:18,760
Pretty cute.

512
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:23,480
Let me tell you my design concept.

513
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:26,360
Go ahead.

514
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:33,960
Gen Z's love for guochao culture,

515
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:36,080
at its core, is really about

516
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:38,320
searching for cultural roots.

517
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:41,040
Without cultural faith to lean on,

518
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:43,320
young people's hearts have nowhere to rest.

519
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:45,760
Xuan paper's thousand-year legacy

520
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:49,080
carries the shared memory of scholars

521
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:50,760
throughout the ages.

522
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:52,200
The Xuan paper you're touching now

523
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:54,480
is the same as what the ancients touched.

524
00:18:54,560 --> 00:18:56,000
It gives you a kind of

525
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:58,840
emotional resonance across time.

526
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:01,040
Acrylic or plastic sheets

527
00:19:01,320 --> 00:19:03,160
could never achieve this effect.

528
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:08,160
You're absolutely right.

529
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:11,280
This is the perfect match

530
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,960
between Xuan paper and modern creative design.

531
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:15,720
Exactly.

532
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:17,280
I knew you'd get me.

533
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,000
What I want is

534
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:22,280
to use a kind of "imperfection healing"

535
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:25,040
to tap into Gen Z's emotions.

536
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:25,960
So look here.

537
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:27,280
In Xuan Bao'er's design,

538
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:28,840
see, there are two little horns,

539
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:31,520
and Zhi Ji's spiky ponytail.

540
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:34,600
It's all about finding unity in contradiction,

541
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:36,440
harmony in chaos,

542
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:39,040
and beauty in disorder,

543
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:40,960
all coming together as the final result.

544
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:42,600
I even deliberately kept

545
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:43,720
some of the rough paper pulp edges.

546
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,440
I want to use this imperfection

547
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:47,760
to offer young people emotional value.

548
00:19:48,240 --> 00:19:49,440
When young people are stuck in the rat race,

549
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:50,600
one look at these

550
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:52,200
and they can just relax.

551
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:53,400
Why?

552
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:57,240
Because their imperfections don't hold back

553
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:58,960
their true self-expression.

554
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:01,520
And they don't hurt their cuteness either.

555
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:03,520
Their flaws

556
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:05,760
are exactly what can ease

557
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:08,360
young people's anxiety about

558
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,480
chasing perfection,

559
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:11,640
creating a healing effect.

560
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:19,360
Don't just look.

561
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:20,800
There's more to it than that.

562
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:21,640
Here.

563
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:22,280
Xuan Yao.

564
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:23,280
Let me show you.

565
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:24,400
I wanted to...

566
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:25,480
Pull this part out.

567
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:27,080
Try it.

568
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:30,960
What do you think?

569
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:31,840
Fun, right?

570
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:34,760
On here,

571
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:36,800
you can write a blessing,

572
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,240
or a complaint,

573
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:39,840
or a snarky comment.

574
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:41,560
And my suggestion?

575
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:42,440
Write this:

576
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:45,720
"No more rat race, grow freely."

577
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:46,760
Clever, right?

578
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:53,920
Very clever indeed.

579
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:55,520
And very creative.

580
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:57,480
Looks like Yiran's words

581
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:59,280
really got through to you.

582
00:20:59,280 --> 00:21:00,280
A hundred words from us

583
00:21:00,280 --> 00:21:02,000
aren't worth one word from her.

584
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:04,640
This is what they call...

585
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:06,600
"Listen to all sides and see clearly."

586
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:10,560
Such an amazing girl,

587
00:21:11,360 --> 00:21:12,840
you'd better not let her slip away.

588
00:21:13,080 --> 00:21:14,440
You've got to make your move fast.

589
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:19,800
Xuan Yao.

590
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:21,760
Wait, you're being really weird today.

591
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:23,520
Xuan Yao.

592
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:24,240
My work is almost dry.

593
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:26,640
I... I need to paint a bit more.

594
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,480
From the chairman's perspective,

595
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:48,160
he's not entirely wrong.

596
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:50,360
You need to consider his last remark.

597
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:53,360
From what angle would you talk to Xuan Yu?

598
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,800
And what would the consequences be?

599
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:57,040
Ms. Xin,

600
00:21:57,960 --> 00:22:00,160
right now you represent the company's interests,

601
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:02,480
and friendship comes second.

602
00:22:03,760 --> 00:22:05,600
Whether from the company's angle

603
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:06,920
or from a friend's angle,

604
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:09,000
you shouldn't lay it all out with him now.

605
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:12,320
Because, as the chairman said,

606
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:14,760
Xuan Yu was a nobody

607
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:16,600
when Dayazhai discovered him.

608
00:22:16,760 --> 00:22:19,200
And the terms you offered are very generous.

609
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:21,200
Partnering with Dayazhai, for Xuan Yu,

610
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,480
is all upside, no downside.

611
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:23,720
Isn't it?

612
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:24,440
Yuqing,

613
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:26,160
what the chairman is doing now

614
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:28,040
is unfair to Xuan Yu.

615
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:31,760
Xuan Yu,

616
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:34,960
the copyright and patent came through.

617
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:36,960
That's great news, great news.

618
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:38,480
It's in my laptop bag.

619
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:40,480
Let me grab it and show you.

620
00:22:40,480 --> 00:22:42,080
It's fine, just keep it with you.

621
00:22:43,480 --> 00:22:44,960
You should take a look anyway.

622
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:46,840
No, really, just keep it.

623
00:22:46,840 --> 00:22:47,960
I'm always losing things.

624
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:49,040
You know that.

625
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:50,400
With you, I feel at ease.

626
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:58,240
Sister Xin,

627
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:00,520
don't dwell on this anymore.

628
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:02,240
It really isn't important.

629
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:03,800
The current partnership

630
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,240
is a win-win for both Xuan Yu

631
00:23:05,240 --> 00:23:06,800
and Dayazhai.

632
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:09,520
If you lay it all out with Xuan Yu now,

633
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:11,240
the outcome

634
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:13,280
would be devastating for both sides.

635
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:15,000
Including you.

636
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:20,320
Xuan Yu, I want to ask you something.

637
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:22,560
Just say what's on your mind.

638
00:23:26,520 --> 00:23:28,160
Xuan Yu, I'm being very serious,

639
00:23:28,160 --> 00:23:30,160
and I hope you'll answer me seriously too.

640
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:30,920
Alright?

641
00:23:44,040 --> 00:23:45,640
Is this serious enough?

642
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:49,960
What I wanted to say is,

643
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,160
do you think

644
00:23:54,040 --> 00:23:55,600
our partnership

645
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:57,560
can make it to the end?

646
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:58,760
What do you mean?

647
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:03,680
I...

648
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:06,680
Let me put it another way.

649
00:24:09,160 --> 00:24:11,480
On the day you achieve success and fame,

650
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:12,760
would you...

651
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:16,760
would you consider giving me up,

652
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:22,280
and, and Dayazhai?

653
00:24:26,040 --> 00:24:27,480
What are you actually trying to say?

654
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:33,640
I think you probably already know.

655
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:37,840
Let me be honest with you.

656
00:24:37,840 --> 00:24:38,480
Xuan Yao, I...

657
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:39,160
Wait.

658
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:43,240
You're not about to confess your feelings, are you?

659
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:45,960
I...

660
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:46,680
Don't say it.

661
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:48,440
Don't say it.

662
00:24:48,640 --> 00:24:50,240
You absolutely can't be thinking that way!

663
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:51,000
Sister Xin.

664
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:53,000
I know you've always thought I'm handsome,

665
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:53,800
and talented too,

666
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:55,160
but the two of us just aren't a match.

667
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:56,280
Sister Xin.

668
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:58,440
Calm down. Stay calm.

669
00:24:58,960 --> 00:24:59,760
No, wait.

670
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:02,320
Xuan Yao, how could you think that?

671
00:25:02,320 --> 00:25:03,600
How could I think that?

672
00:25:03,600 --> 00:25:05,200
Before, we'd get right down to business.

673
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:06,240
Today you're hemming and hawing,

674
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:07,320
can't get anything out straight,

675
00:25:07,320 --> 00:25:08,960
and you're using Lin Yiran to test me.

676
00:25:08,960 --> 00:25:10,600
Isn't that clearly jealousy?

677
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:12,520
No, I'm not, Xuan Yao.

678
00:25:12,520 --> 00:25:13,200
Okay, okay, okay.

679
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:13,920
You're not, fine.

680
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:14,840
Let's just say you're not.

681
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:16,480
Just, just not, you're just not.

682
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:17,440
No.

683
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:18,800
That's not right, not right, Xuan Yao.

684
00:25:18,800 --> 00:25:19,480
What?

685
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:21,600
What do you mean, "let's just say you're not"?

686
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:21,920
You...

687
00:25:21,920 --> 00:25:22,760
It's really nothing.

688
00:25:22,760 --> 00:25:23,280
Come on.

689
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:24,920
Let's keep today's stuff to ourselves.

690
00:25:25,080 --> 00:25:25,680
What?

691
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:26,680
What do you mean, keep to ourselves?

692
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:27,280
It's nothing. Let's each do our own thing.

693
00:25:27,280 --> 00:25:28,200
Xuan Yao, I...

694
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:28,840
No, Sister Xin, Sister Xin.

695
00:25:28,840 --> 00:25:29,560
I really do have something to tell you.

696
00:25:29,560 --> 00:25:30,920
Brother Min absolutely can't find out about this.

697
00:25:30,920 --> 00:25:31,520
If Brother Min finds out, I'm dead.

698
00:25:31,520 --> 00:25:31,960
No, Xuan Yao, listen to me.

699
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:33,000
I won't let him find out about this.

700
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:33,680
I get it, I totally...

701
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:34,760
But I really do have something to say.

702
00:25:34,760 --> 00:25:35,960
Okay, okay, I'm not...

703
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:36,040
No.

704
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:36,720
Isn't it nothing?

705
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:37,920
It's nothing. You do your thing, I'll do mine.

706
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:38,840
Xuan Yao, listen to me.

707
00:25:38,840 --> 00:25:39,480
I know, Sister Xin, I know.

708
00:25:39,480 --> 00:25:40,400
Got it. Bye-bye.

709
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:41,240
Bye-bye.

710
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:42,840
Xuan Yao, Xuan Yao!

711
00:25:42,840 --> 00:25:43,520
Xuan Yao, open the door!

712
00:25:43,520 --> 00:25:44,840
We're still good friends!

713
00:25:45,080 --> 00:25:47,280
We're good friends, so open the door!

714
00:25:47,760 --> 00:25:49,760
I'm not done talking, Xuan Yao!

715
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:52,600
Xuan Yao, open the door!

716
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:55,840
This is insane.

717
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:00,680
What just happened?

718
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:03,720
How did the talk end up like this?

719
00:26:07,760 --> 00:26:08,600
As for this venue,

720
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:10,640
I'd like it to be a Guochao exhibit area.

721
00:26:10,680 --> 00:26:12,560
There are two themes here that need

722
00:26:12,560 --> 00:26:13,920
AR technology support.

723
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,960
One is an AR treasure hunt game,

724
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:17,720
and an AR ink painting theater.

725
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:19,360
For the treasure hunt game,

726
00:26:19,360 --> 00:26:22,160
I may need a five-dimensional level design.

727
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,280
Here's our proposal.

728
00:26:23,280 --> 00:26:24,280
You can take a look.

729
00:26:24,680 --> 00:26:26,400
As for the VR ink theater,

730
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:29,800
I want to base it on "A Thousand Li of Rivers and Mountains."

731
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:31,320
Through VR equipment,

732
00:26:31,320 --> 00:26:33,760
viewers can, in a virtual space,

733
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:36,280
interact with ink painting elements.

734
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:38,760
For example, through gestures, right?

735
00:26:38,760 --> 00:26:40,960
To control the ink's flow, diffusion,

736
00:26:40,960 --> 00:26:42,400
and other dynamic effects.

737
00:26:44,760 --> 00:26:45,960
The technology can handle it.

738
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:47,360
The venue's no problem.

739
00:26:47,680 --> 00:26:48,840
The timeline can be managed.

740
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:50,240
The equipment is all ready-made.

741
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:51,480
The main work

742
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:52,840
is, based on the specific environment,

743
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:54,480
doing 3D modeling and rendering.

744
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:57,720
We'll bring in extra people to work overtime.

745
00:26:57,800 --> 00:26:58,760
We can get it done in time.

746
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:01,720
Also, during your design process,

747
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:02,840
we need to track it all the way through,

748
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:04,040
to avoid any mistakes.

749
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:06,160
After all, time's tight and the workload is heavy.

750
00:27:06,160 --> 00:27:08,200
What's our budget?

751
00:27:09,760 --> 00:27:11,040
What's your quote?

752
00:27:11,720 --> 00:27:12,680
To be honest,

753
00:27:12,920 --> 00:27:14,840
your event concept is really great.

754
00:27:14,840 --> 00:27:15,760
If done well,

755
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:18,200
it could be a standout project for our company too.

756
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:18,840
Right.

757
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:20,040
As for the price,

758
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:21,440
no exaggeration,

759
00:27:22,520 --> 00:27:23,200
600,000.

760
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:27,600
Sorry, Mr. Qi,

761
00:27:27,840 --> 00:27:29,760
let me be honest with you too.

762
00:27:29,760 --> 00:27:31,360
Your quote

763
00:27:31,360 --> 00:27:33,040
and our budget have a gap,

764
00:27:33,240 --> 00:27:34,600
and it's a bit big.

765
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:37,000
How big?

766
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:38,720
Well, it's still in ten-thousands.

767
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,240
It's between six and ten.

768
00:27:41,440 --> 00:27:42,680
We can only pick one.

769
00:27:43,160 --> 00:27:46,240
So that's 60,000 or 100,000.

770
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:48,160
Right.

771
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:52,320
Director Lin, no need to see me out.

772
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:54,320
Then we'll wait for your final confirmation.

773
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:55,240
No problem.

774
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:56,480
Looking forward to a great collaboration.

775
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:11,760
I was sure he'd never agree.

776
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:15,160
Didn't expect we'd land a 100,000 cost fee.

777
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:17,600
That profit-sharing model between both sides,

778
00:28:18,760 --> 00:28:20,960
Director Lin sure sold the dream well.

779
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:24,320
Teacher Qi's probably dreaming sweet in the car.

780
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:25,360
Sister Yiran.

781
00:28:25,360 --> 00:28:27,200
I think when we hold the big event,

782
00:28:27,200 --> 00:28:29,800
red flags waving, crowds everywhere,

783
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:31,960
gongs and drums blaring, firecrackers popping.

784
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:34,160
Where'd you get all these phrases?

785
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:35,560
Let's all work hard together.

786
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:37,560
Maybe we can help Teacher Qi's dream

787
00:28:37,560 --> 00:28:38,480
become reality.

788
00:28:39,240 --> 00:28:40,000
Sister Yi.

789
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:41,800
If we negotiate it this way,

790
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:44,160
we should pass the money gatekeepers, right?

791
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:45,560
Our finance office

792
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:47,760
only ensures special funds are used properly.

793
00:28:47,760 --> 00:28:49,520
As long as it stays within budget,

794
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:51,320
Director Huang can't find fault with it.

795
00:28:51,320 --> 00:28:52,080
Don't worry.

796
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:52,920
See that?

797
00:28:52,920 --> 00:28:54,160
Sister Yi always has my back.

798
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:55,920
Alright, let's hurry

799
00:28:55,920 --> 00:28:57,960
and go check on the stationery exhibit setup.

800
00:28:57,960 --> 00:28:59,640
Handle what we can first.

801
00:28:59,640 --> 00:29:01,200
Once the Guochao zone opens,

802
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:02,240
we definitely won't have time.

803
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:03,200
Hurry, let's go.

804
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:05,800
Sister Yiran.

805
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:07,720
Don't bother going.

806
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:08,840
I just came from over there.

807
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:10,080
Nobody's there.

808
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:12,160
Wait, how can nobody be there?

809
00:29:12,680 --> 00:29:13,480
Hold on.

810
00:29:13,480 --> 00:29:14,840
I sent notice in the group chat.

811
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:16,480
There should be at least three teams, ten people.

812
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,840
Two showed up in the morning.

813
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:21,160
Left at noon.

814
00:29:21,160 --> 00:29:22,920
Not a single one came in the afternoon.

815
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:25,040
What's the reason then?

816
00:29:25,440 --> 00:29:26,240
Sister Yiran,

817
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:28,040
if you're asking, I'll be honest.

818
00:29:28,160 --> 00:29:29,480
Who actually wants to come?

819
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:31,640
It's a team thrown together from different departments.

820
00:29:31,640 --> 00:29:33,040
Everyone's swamped with their own work,

821
00:29:33,040 --> 00:29:34,480
and still has to run over here daily.

822
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:36,040
And when they get here, nothing's provided.

823
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:37,840
Water? Buy it yourself.

824
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:39,200
Meals? Go back to town.

825
00:29:39,480 --> 00:29:40,720
The office cars are all in use.

826
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:42,640
So they drive themselves or take cabs.

827
00:29:42,960 --> 00:29:45,000
We're all working. Let's understand each other.

828
00:29:45,040 --> 00:29:46,240
Aren't we both in the same boat?

829
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:47,240
Look at these past few days,

830
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,480
which day haven't we worked overtime?

831
00:29:48,760 --> 00:29:50,480
This, this, this is originally

832
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:51,720
your Economic Development Office's job.

833
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:53,480
Nobody else asked for this event.

834
00:29:53,480 --> 00:29:54,840
That's going too far, don't you think?

835
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:56,480
What do you mean it's our office's job?

836
00:29:57,200 --> 00:29:59,480
This is Taohua Town's top priority right now.

837
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:00,840
If you've got complaints,

838
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:02,480
go tell Secretary Peng or Deputy Mayor Luo.

839
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:03,400
Don't dump it on us.

840
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:04,200
Taozi, okay, okay.

841
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:06,280
Don't blow up at me, I did show up.

842
00:30:06,960 --> 00:30:08,840
I'm just voicing what everyone thinks.

843
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:11,720
Yiran, I need to head back too.

844
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:13,080
The county audit bureau is coming.

845
00:30:13,080 --> 00:30:15,040
I have to go clean up the books first.

846
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:15,840
Understood.

847
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:17,240
Thanks for your work, Sister Yi. Head back.

848
00:30:17,240 --> 00:30:18,080
Bye, Sister Yi.

849
00:30:19,600 --> 00:30:21,040
I'll post a notice in the group chat now.

850
00:30:21,240 --> 00:30:22,200
Anyone not here within twenty minutes,

851
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:23,400
I'll report every one of them to the leaders.

852
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:24,760
Enough, Taozi, don't send it.

853
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:26,840
Post a notice in the group

854
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:28,280
that starting tomorrow,

855
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:29,280
everyone moves their stuff over here.

856
00:30:29,280 --> 00:30:30,600
From now on, we work on-site.

857
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:32,480
As for the meal issue,

858
00:30:33,280 --> 00:30:35,600
I'll coordinate with Deputy Mayor Luo.

859
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:37,760
Will, will that actually work?

860
00:30:37,760 --> 00:30:38,920
Work or not, it has to work.

861
00:30:39,280 --> 00:30:40,720
Alright, you two get back to work.

862
00:30:41,040 --> 00:30:42,080
I'm off to find Deputy Mayor Luo.

863
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:50,520
Alright then.

864
00:30:50,520 --> 00:30:51,080
Don't worry.

865
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:52,000
Deputy Mayor Luo.

866
00:30:53,440 --> 00:30:54,360
Director Lin is here.

867
00:30:54,480 --> 00:30:55,400
You go ahead, go on.

868
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:56,080
Okay, okay.

869
00:30:57,680 --> 00:30:58,480
Deputy Mayor Luo,

870
00:31:01,320 --> 00:31:02,800
I know what you want to say.

871
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:05,000
I still have to get things done here.

872
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:07,840
I can't reassign the staff.

873
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:09,160
It takes a leader at your level

874
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:10,080
to step in and handle it.

875
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:12,760
Even so, I have to be gentle with them,

876
00:31:12,760 --> 00:31:14,200
talk it through nicely.

877
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:16,040
Isn't that how this job works?

878
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:18,040
Whatever you do, you need the right approach,

879
00:31:18,040 --> 00:31:18,720
don't you?

880
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:19,440
I think you must

881
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:20,840
hold a general meeting for everyone.

882
00:31:20,840 --> 00:31:22,440
Time waits for no one now.

883
00:31:22,680 --> 00:31:23,120
Fine.

884
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:24,480
Here's the thing.

885
00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:25,440
I've still got a

886
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:26,840
very important reception to handle.

887
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:28,360
Once it's done, I'll head over.

888
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:30,240
Including the on-site office and

889
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:31,040
meal arrangement you mentioned,

890
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:33,360
Secretary Peng has already applied for funds.

891
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:34,160
It's just that the town's budget

892
00:31:34,160 --> 00:31:35,440
is being squeezed out like toothpaste,

893
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:36,480
a bit here, a bit there.

894
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:37,640
I'm sure you're well aware.

895
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:38,240
So here's the deal.

896
00:31:38,240 --> 00:31:39,840
For now, just make do.

897
00:31:39,840 --> 00:31:40,760
It's only temporary.

898
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:42,280
Wait, wait.

899
00:31:42,360 --> 00:31:43,640
So your reception matters,

900
00:31:43,640 --> 00:31:45,440
but the Four Treasures Festival doesn't?

901
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:49,760
And my work,

902
00:31:49,840 --> 00:31:51,760
now you're the one arranging it, huh?

903
00:31:53,640 --> 00:31:54,400
What a joke.

904
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:56,560
Master Huang, let's go.

905
00:31:59,800 --> 00:32:01,440
Aren't you something.

906
00:32:08,280 --> 00:32:08,920
Secretary,

907
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:12,080
coordinating multiple departments is really tough.

908
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:14,320
If Deputy Mayor Luo doesn't step in,

909
00:32:14,960 --> 00:32:16,840
Lin Yiran alone can hardly solve this.

910
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:19,560
No rush, no rush. Let's wait and see.

911
00:32:19,840 --> 00:32:21,680
The opening date's been reported to the higher-ups,

912
00:32:21,680 --> 00:32:22,960
and the ads have already gone out.

913
00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:25,000
A whole week's flown by,

914
00:32:25,240 --> 00:32:27,000
I'm afraid there's no more time to wait.

915
00:32:27,080 --> 00:32:28,080
Don't worry.

916
00:32:29,240 --> 00:32:31,280
What can't be accomplished?

917
00:32:32,040 --> 00:32:34,040
Let Lin Yiran sweat it out a bit.

918
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:35,240
It won't hurt her.

919
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:37,840
As the popular saying goes these days,

920
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:39,760
let the bullets fly a while longer.

921
00:32:41,240 --> 00:32:41,960
Secretary,

922
00:32:42,480 --> 00:32:44,800
your composure is truly beyond ours.

923
00:32:44,800 --> 00:32:45,760
Once you've been through enough,

924
00:32:45,760 --> 00:32:46,880
your composure improves.

925
00:32:47,280 --> 00:32:49,200
For me, for you, for Lin Yiran,

926
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:49,960
it's all the same.

927
00:32:50,320 --> 00:32:51,000
Understood.

928
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:52,360
Alright, Secretary.

929
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:53,120
I'll get back to work then.

930
00:32:53,120 --> 00:32:53,880
Alright, go on.

931
00:32:56,080 --> 00:32:56,680
Set it down.

932
00:32:57,200 --> 00:32:58,080
Down, down.

933
00:32:58,880 --> 00:33:00,440
Master, careful, slow down, slow down.

934
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:02,600
Careful not to scratch it.

935
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:04,560
Yes, yes.

936
00:33:05,080 --> 00:33:06,040
Where's Lu Bingguo?

937
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:08,640
He had something come up,

938
00:33:08,640 --> 00:33:09,880
so he told me to come cover for a bit.

939
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:12,400
How can you keep swapping assigned duties?

940
00:33:12,600 --> 00:33:13,800
Well, he had something to do.

941
00:33:15,280 --> 00:33:16,320
Yesterday I told him

942
00:33:16,320 --> 00:33:18,000
we need at least 15 workers today.

943
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:19,040
Did he tell you that?

944
00:33:19,760 --> 00:33:20,400
No, he didn't.

945
00:33:21,680 --> 00:33:22,280
Then did he tell you

946
00:33:22,280 --> 00:33:24,000
how these banners should be arranged?

947
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:25,080
No, he didn't.

948
00:33:25,280 --> 00:33:26,680
Then what are you supervising here? Tell me.

949
00:33:26,960 --> 00:33:28,080
I have no idea.

950
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:29,880
He called me at noon to come over,

951
00:33:29,880 --> 00:33:31,000
so I just came.

952
00:33:32,600 --> 00:33:33,320
Fine.

953
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:34,480
Then just stand around here.

954
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:37,200
Okay.

955
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:38,600
These two.

956
00:33:39,480 --> 00:33:40,400
Sister Taozi,

957
00:33:41,080 --> 00:33:42,640
I really have to head back.

958
00:33:42,640 --> 00:33:44,680
Any later and I'll be late for the meeting.

959
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:46,320
The boss just told me to drop by briefly.

960
00:33:46,720 --> 00:33:48,400
But your work here isn't done.

961
00:33:48,480 --> 00:33:49,960
And you're a member of the execution team,

962
00:33:49,960 --> 00:33:51,000
so you answer to the execution team.

963
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:52,520
Well,

964
00:33:52,520 --> 00:33:54,040
that's true in theory,

965
00:33:54,200 --> 00:33:56,400
but will I stay on the execution team forever?

966
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:57,480
Once this is over,

967
00:33:57,480 --> 00:33:59,080
I'll still have to go back to my original department.

968
00:33:59,440 --> 00:34:01,040
But right now you're still on the execution team.

969
00:34:01,040 --> 00:34:02,560
You can't just not care about this, right?

970
00:34:02,760 --> 00:34:04,640
Honestly, Sister Taozi,

971
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:07,200
you've got to consider our position too.

972
00:34:07,320 --> 00:34:08,040
Right now, we're

973
00:34:08,040 --> 00:34:09,480
like a mouse in a bellows,

974
00:34:09,480 --> 00:34:10,520
getting squeezed from both sides.

975
00:34:10,520 --> 00:34:11,960
I really have no way out right now.

976
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:12,719
Director Lin,

977
00:34:12,760 --> 00:34:14,280
the materials you asked me to send to the online platform,

978
00:34:14,280 --> 00:34:15,280
I've sent them all.

979
00:34:16,199 --> 00:34:17,760
Um, I...

980
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:19,679
Got it. Good work. You can go.

981
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:21,000
Thank you, Director Lin.

982
00:34:24,320 --> 00:34:25,719
And you two? Anything going on?

983
00:34:27,840 --> 00:34:28,960
If, if we could leave,

984
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:29,480
that'd be great.

985
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:30,600
Understood. Go on back.

986
00:34:31,239 --> 00:34:32,320
I've got another meeting.

987
00:34:46,840 --> 00:34:48,159
So you're just letting them leave?

988
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:50,080
What else can I do?

989
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:54,600
Even if you made them stay,

990
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:55,840
they'd only resent it.

991
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:56,679
What's the point?

992
00:34:57,840 --> 00:34:59,760
When Secretary Peng comes, everyone shows up.

993
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:00,800
When she doesn't come,

994
00:35:00,800 --> 00:35:02,760
it's always this scattered turnout.

995
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:03,600
Even when they do show up,

996
00:35:03,600 --> 00:35:05,880
it's a different person every day.

997
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:09,080
How can we get any work done like this?

998
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,040
Sister Yiran,

999
00:35:11,320 --> 00:35:12,640
it's time to put that clever mind of yours

1000
00:35:12,640 --> 00:35:13,640
to work and think of something.

1001
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:17,200
Otherwise, if this keeps up, I feel like...

1002
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:20,400
Head back to town.

1003
00:35:20,720 --> 00:35:22,000
Tell them there's a meeting this afternoon.

1004
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:22,640
Okay.

1005
00:35:23,200 --> 00:35:24,000
What's the topic?

1006
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:25,720
An implementation work meeting.

1007
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:28,240
Implementation work meeting?

1008
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:30,400
The same one we hold every day?

1009
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:31,480
I don't think it'll do any good.

1010
00:35:31,480 --> 00:35:33,880
Just do as I say, alright?

1011
00:35:34,200 --> 00:35:35,280
Okay, whatever you say.

1012
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:36,240
What time?

1013
00:35:36,560 --> 00:35:38,080
As for the time, wait for me to let you know.

1014
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:39,440
Okay.

1015
00:35:41,880 --> 00:35:42,760
Hello, Director Ge?

1016
00:35:43,520 --> 00:35:44,760
Yes, that's right.

1017
00:35:45,120 --> 00:35:46,680
I might need a favor from you.

1018
00:35:58,240 --> 00:35:59,040
Sister Yiran,

1019
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:00,360
look,

1020
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:01,800
only a handful of us have shown up.

1021
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:03,440
Are we still going ahead with this meeting?

1022
00:36:03,720 --> 00:36:04,960
What's going on here?

1023
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:06,360
Where are all the others?

1024
00:36:06,480 --> 00:36:07,600
Why haven't they arrived yet?

1025
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:08,360
Everyone,

1026
00:36:08,720 --> 00:36:10,280
I really don't get it.

1027
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:11,840
What are we waiting for?

1028
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:14,640
Yiran, are we doing this or not?

1029
00:36:14,920 --> 00:36:15,720
Just a bit longer.

1030
00:36:16,480 --> 00:36:17,320
Fine.

1031
00:36:18,640 --> 00:36:19,480
Alright.

1032
00:36:19,640 --> 00:36:20,840
Let's all take a look first

1033
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:22,400
at the proposal in front of you.

1034
00:36:22,440 --> 00:36:24,320
Many sections have been revised.

1035
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:26,120
We need to get familiar with the plan

1036
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:27,480
so we can carry it out properly.

1037
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:30,120
Director Lin,

1038
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:31,600
let's just get started.

1039
00:36:31,920 --> 00:36:33,960
I've got a report to write later.

1040
00:36:36,080 --> 00:36:36,920
Director Lin,

1041
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:38,840
Secretary Peng is waiting for your revised

1042
00:36:38,840 --> 00:36:40,840
plan for the Four Treasures Culture Festival.

1043
00:36:40,840 --> 00:36:42,520
She has to report to the county at three.

1044
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:43,560
Hurry it up!

1045
00:36:43,720 --> 00:36:44,800
Sorry about that, Director Ge.

1046
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:46,160
I'll head over as soon as I'm done here.

1047
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:47,960
Please let Secretary Peng know.

1048
00:36:48,640 --> 00:36:49,280
Alright.

1049
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:51,760
Not answering their phones either.

1050
00:36:57,040 --> 00:36:59,120
I want to say a few words about discipline.

1051
00:36:59,560 --> 00:37:00,400
First of all,

1052
00:37:01,080 --> 00:37:02,680
I owe everyone an apology.

1053
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:04,920
Because this Four Treasures Culture Festival

1054
00:37:05,080 --> 00:37:06,400
was proposed by me.

1055
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:08,840
But this isn't just my concern alone.

1056
00:37:09,360 --> 00:37:10,640
It's the whole of Taohua Town's.

1057
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:12,760
And Secretary Peng has repeatedly stressed

1058
00:37:12,840 --> 00:37:14,640
we must go all out and treat it as a priority.

1059
00:37:14,640 --> 00:37:15,440
Well said.

1060
00:37:16,680 --> 00:37:17,480
How's that?

1061
00:37:18,520 --> 00:37:19,760
Secretary Peng.

1062
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:21,480
Sit, sit, everyone sit down.

1063
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:22,680
Here are the documents you asked for.

1064
00:37:22,680 --> 00:37:23,440
Good.

1065
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:31,440
Only this handful of people showed up?

1066
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:32,880
Secretary Peng.

1067
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:35,680
This is the fullest turnout we've had.

1068
00:37:35,960 --> 00:37:38,400
These days, we can't get anyone to show up.

1069
00:37:38,680 --> 00:37:39,800
Nothing we say makes a difference.

1070
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:41,640
The whole schedule is falling behind.

1071
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:47,160
This just won't do.

1072
00:37:49,360 --> 00:37:50,960
How many times have I said this?

1073
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:53,120
The Four Treasures Festival

1074
00:37:53,120 --> 00:37:54,600
is right now our town's

1075
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:56,160
top priority of all priorities.

1076
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:58,360
So these comrades who skipped the meeting,

1077
00:37:58,360 --> 00:37:59,440
what's that supposed to mean?

1078
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:01,320
Lin Yiran.

1079
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:04,320
Starting today,

1080
00:38:04,520 --> 00:38:06,280
we crack down completely, once and for all.

1081
00:38:06,280 --> 00:38:08,120
Director Ge, take the absentee list

1082
00:38:08,120 --> 00:38:09,280
and compile it for me.

1083
00:38:09,440 --> 00:38:10,400
If it happens again,

1084
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:10,720
they lose their annual honors eligibility.

1085
00:38:10,720 --> 00:38:11,680
They lose their annual honors eligibility.

1086
00:38:11,680 --> 00:38:13,360
They lose their annual honors eligibility.

1087
00:38:13,360 --> 00:38:14,080
Understood.

1088
00:38:14,360 --> 00:38:15,400
If there's any problem,

1089
00:38:15,520 --> 00:38:17,840
send the department heads to my office.

1090
00:38:17,880 --> 00:38:19,160
I refuse to believe

1091
00:38:19,600 --> 00:38:23,000
they'll keep ignoring the town's directives.

1092
00:38:23,400 --> 00:38:24,320
What's the meaning of this?

1093
00:38:24,440 --> 00:38:25,720
Um, Secretary Peng,

1094
00:38:25,720 --> 00:38:27,840
I believe everyone has real difficulties.

1095
00:38:27,840 --> 00:38:28,520
Right?

1096
00:38:28,600 --> 00:38:30,160
Yesterday on-site I even saw

1097
00:38:30,160 --> 00:38:31,280
you all squeezing in every spare moment

1098
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:32,400
to handle your regular duties.

1099
00:38:32,400 --> 00:38:33,200
Two jobs on one person's shoulders,

1100
00:38:33,200 --> 00:38:34,320
that's really not easy.

1101
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:36,240
Next time I'll keep a closer watch.

1102
00:38:36,240 --> 00:38:37,880
This can't be allowed to happen again.

1103
00:38:37,880 --> 00:38:39,520
You'll all cooperate with my work from now on,

1104
00:38:39,520 --> 00:38:40,040
right?

1105
00:38:40,040 --> 00:38:40,880
Cooperate, cooperate.

1106
00:38:40,880 --> 00:38:41,840
Cooperate, fully cooperate.

1107
00:38:41,840 --> 00:38:42,600
Secretary Peng,

1108
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:44,800
I'll ensure this event runs smoothly.

1109
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:45,960
If anything goes wrong,

1110
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:46,960
you can hold me accountable.

1111
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:48,120
Good.

1112
00:38:48,920 --> 00:38:50,480
Let's do as Director Lin says.

1113
00:38:51,040 --> 00:38:52,560
I don't want a next time.

1114
00:38:53,560 --> 00:38:54,360
Secretary Peng.

1115
00:38:55,160 --> 00:38:55,960
Get back to work.

1116
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:04,240
All right.

1117
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:06,920
You've all seen Secretary Peng's stance.

1118
00:39:07,240 --> 00:39:09,760
I hope you'll pass the word around.

1119
00:39:09,760 --> 00:39:10,680
Let this be a warning.

1120
00:39:10,800 --> 00:39:12,400
I can plead your case once,

1121
00:39:12,600 --> 00:39:13,720
but not a second time.

1122
00:39:14,280 --> 00:39:17,200
I don't want anyone losing their honors later,

1123
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:19,160
and dragging your department heads down,

1124
00:39:19,160 --> 00:39:20,280
getting them reprimanded, right?

1125
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:21,960
Nobody wants to see that outcome.

1126
00:39:23,440 --> 00:39:25,520
All right, carry on.

1127
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:28,600
Look at her.

1128
00:39:31,720 --> 00:39:33,000
This young lady

1129
00:39:33,040 --> 00:39:34,520
is really sharp as a tack.

1130
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:36,400
She's getting smarter and smarter.

1131
00:39:36,520 --> 00:39:38,400
It's all thanks to the Secretary's guidance.

1132
00:39:38,680 --> 00:39:39,760
Director Liao was just saying

1133
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:41,280
that Lin Yiran wasn't making progress.

1134
00:39:41,320 --> 00:39:42,800
Well, she's come a long way now, hasn't she?

1135
00:39:42,800 --> 00:39:43,000
She's come a long way now, hasn't she?

1136
00:39:43,040 --> 00:39:45,240
Her mind is sharper. That counts as progress.

1137
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:46,560
Yes indeed.

1138
00:39:46,560 --> 00:39:47,520
Director Ge, go get back to work.

1139
00:39:47,520 --> 00:39:48,560
Okay, okay, goodbye.

1140
00:39:55,440 --> 00:39:56,400
Where have you been?

1141
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:57,160
Slow down.

1142
00:39:57,960 --> 00:39:59,200
Why'd you buy so many snacks?

1143
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:00,080
For me?

1144
00:40:00,680 --> 00:40:01,640
Here, take these.

1145
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:04,960
Go hand them out to the folks on site.

1146
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:07,160
You're really something.

1147
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:08,680
You just put them on the spot,

1148
00:40:08,680 --> 00:40:10,120
and now you're sweetening the deal.

1149
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:13,120
Tell the logistics staff

1150
00:40:13,120 --> 00:40:14,200
that starting tomorrow,

1151
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:15,920
prepare bottled water and boxed meals.

1152
00:40:15,920 --> 00:40:16,920
As for the water,

1153
00:40:16,920 --> 00:40:18,800
prepare triple the headcount.

1154
00:40:18,960 --> 00:40:20,360
Refill anytime it runs low.

1155
00:40:20,880 --> 00:40:23,320
For the meals, go with a three-to-four ratio.

1156
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:24,440
Just in case someone doesn't get enough.

1157
00:40:24,440 --> 00:40:25,200
Okay.

1158
00:40:25,520 --> 00:40:26,520
But there's one issue.

1159
00:40:26,520 --> 00:40:28,400
We don't have enough in our account.

1160
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:29,680
They promised us 60,000,

1161
00:40:29,680 --> 00:40:31,000
but we've only got 15,000 now.

1162
00:40:31,400 --> 00:40:32,760
Every time we ask Deputy Mayor Luo,

1163
00:40:32,880 --> 00:40:34,000
it's just delay after delay.

1164
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:35,640
He doesn't care if we sink or swim.

1165
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:38,720
Just have them prepare it.

1166
00:40:38,720 --> 00:40:40,680
If it's not enough, have them come to me.

1167
00:40:40,920 --> 00:40:41,920
What's going on?

1168
00:40:42,240 --> 00:40:43,840
Why so confident all of a sudden?

1169
00:40:44,520 --> 00:40:45,920
I'll cover it myself first.

1170
00:40:46,160 --> 00:40:48,360
Just reimburse me after payday.

1171
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:50,240
Okay then.

1172
00:40:50,760 --> 00:40:51,720
All right, I've got to go.

1173
00:40:51,720 --> 00:40:52,680
I've got something to do.

1174
00:40:52,680 --> 00:40:53,200
I'm heading out.

1175
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:54,040
Where are you going?

1176
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:54,760
Wait...

1177
00:40:56,720 --> 00:40:58,160
The AR Ink Spirit Treasure Hunt

1178
00:40:58,160 --> 00:40:59,840
and the Ink Wash Theater segments,

1179
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:02,120
I've contracted professional companies.

1180
00:41:02,280 --> 00:41:04,760
But what I value most is the Scholars' Gathering.

1181
00:41:04,760 --> 00:41:07,280
Through the interactions,

1182
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:10,000
people can learn more about Xuan paper and the Four Treasures.

1183
00:41:11,800 --> 00:41:12,600
And then?

1184
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:13,800
And then...

1185
00:41:13,800 --> 00:41:14,560
Right.

1186
00:41:14,760 --> 00:41:16,080
Why are you telling me all this?

1187
00:41:18,360 --> 00:41:20,600
Our design setup here

1188
00:41:20,600 --> 00:41:22,000
is kind of, you know, lacking

1189
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:23,640
So we'd like to ask you

1190
00:41:24,160 --> 00:41:25,040
to help us out,

1191
00:41:25,040 --> 00:41:27,640
you brilliant designer who works miracles

1192
00:41:27,880 --> 00:41:28,680
right?

1193
00:41:29,240 --> 00:41:30,640
Don't try that on me.

1194
00:41:31,440 --> 00:41:32,640
Some people, you know,

1195
00:41:33,280 --> 00:41:35,080
nobody likes it when they act cute,

1196
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:37,320
so they'd easily agree to her terms

1197
00:41:37,320 --> 00:41:38,320
just to make her leave.

1198
00:41:38,600 --> 00:41:39,840
But you're different.

1199
00:41:39,880 --> 00:41:42,280
The more you act cute, the less I'll agree,

1200
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:44,040
because I want to enjoy it a bit longer.

1201
00:41:45,880 --> 00:41:47,200
So by your logic,

1202
00:41:47,880 --> 00:41:49,000
I might as well contact Director Liao.

1203
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:50,160
I'll have him give you a call.

1204
00:41:50,160 --> 00:41:50,960
No, no, no.

1205
00:41:51,440 --> 00:41:52,400
Don't contact him.

1206
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:53,960
I don't want to hear him lecture me.

1207
00:41:54,520 --> 00:41:55,400
Let's talk business.

1208
00:41:55,400 --> 00:41:56,360
I agree to help you.

1209
00:41:57,040 --> 00:41:58,400
No more business. I'm done.

1210
00:41:58,520 --> 00:41:59,320
That's it.

1211
00:42:01,120 --> 00:42:03,000
How should the scene be designed?

1212
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:04,360
Just tell me directly.

1213
00:42:04,360 --> 00:42:05,480
Because we have no money.

1214
00:42:10,560 --> 00:42:12,560
You know, you're quite something.

1215
00:42:12,840 --> 00:42:14,920
Asking for freebies and still so righteous about it.

1216
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:20,440
Well, if you won't help, then forget it.

1217
00:42:20,480 --> 00:42:22,760
I'll just go back and tell my boss.

1218
00:42:23,280 --> 00:42:24,040
Tell them

1219
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:26,600
my ideas are childish,

1220
00:42:26,960 --> 00:42:28,560
detached from reality,

1221
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:31,920
immature in thinking,

1222
00:42:35,160 --> 00:42:37,280
unreasonable, and thick-skinned.

1223
00:42:37,440 --> 00:42:38,880
I need to deeply reflect on all this

1224
00:42:38,880 --> 00:42:40,160
and do some serious self-criticism.

1225
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:43,760
Alright, go ahead and say it.

1226
00:42:44,040 --> 00:42:45,160
Money, we really don't have.

1227
00:42:45,160 --> 00:42:46,360
The project, we really want to do.

1228
00:42:46,360 --> 00:42:47,960
How can you help me?

1229
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:50,320
Well, if you're asking a favor, show some attitude.

1230
00:42:51,960 --> 00:42:53,320
With my handsome looks

1231
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:54,200
and noble soul,

1232
00:42:54,200 --> 00:42:55,680
don't I deserve a little praise?

1233
00:42:56,160 --> 00:42:57,440
Praise, huh?

1234
00:42:58,920 --> 00:42:59,440
Fine.
